"instance, if your |TS| host resides on a private network in the "
"10.1.1.0/24 IPv4 address space listening on the address 10.1.1.10, "
"separate from its public interface(s) used to serve client requests, you "
"could add the following remap configuration::"
msgstr ""

# cf25de37f54547f282d10445744d2772
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/statistics/accessing.en.rst:114
msgid ""
"The above configuration sets the default policy for the entirety of IPv4 "
"address space to deny, but then exempts the 10.1.1.0/24 network by "
"permitting their requests to be processed by |TS|. If your monitoring "
"infrastructure makes use of locally-installed data collection agents, you"
" may even wish to restrict access to the Stats Over HTTP plugin to all "
"but localhost."
msgstr ""

